An All Progressives Congress, APC, Presidential aspirant, Bola Tinubu, has distanced himself from making fake promises to Nigerians. Tinubu said he was not one of those aspirants who make fake promises to Nigerians, stressing that not everyone can become President. Speaking with APC delegates in Katsina on Monday, Tinubu stated that he had the experience to resolve the challenges bedeviling Nigeria. Also Read: 2023: Jonathan Disowns Northern Group, says APC Form Bought Without His Consent The APC National Leader vowed to ensure unity among Nigerians. He said: “Anybody can run for the presidency but not everybody can be the President. I am extremely different from other candidates who promise fake agenda. “I am contesting to change the country for good and I say you will never regret giving me your support.”